description:
Fifteen-year-old Peter, a Christian behind the Iron Curtain, is forced to make a choice as he struggles to remain loyal to the Gospel.

This classic from "cold war" communist East Germany is the full-length drama about fifteen-year-old Peter, a Christian behind the Iron Curtain. He is forced to decide between what is "correct" and what is true as he struggles to remain loyal to the Gospel. An older film with new significance since the reunification of Germany. B&W

Director: Stuart Rosenberg
Starring: Michael Gwynn, Christian deBresson, Almut Eggert, Margaret Jahnen
